Trips are not merely a bus ride from A to B but include side trips to hidden gems around local communities, which vary with the weather and the whim of the group. All this while sharing experiences and conversations with new friends, keeping the participants interested and active, thus contributing to quality of life and good health, avoiding the incidence of isolation, anxiety and illness/depression which are a risk for retirees.

DO YOU HAVE FAMILY COMING AND YOU HAVE TO WORK. WHY NOT SEND THEM OUT FOR SOME FUN ON MY BUS. SIGN THEM UP ON A DAY TRIP.
MEMBERSHIP NOT NEEDED.

Details & description:
Rob Janssen has always had an interest in all things mechanical - from his very first hot rod cars and motorcycles, to heavy duty equipment, farm machinery, and everything in between. In 1994 Rob Janssen established R.E.Cycle in Chemainus on Vancouver Island. It's not like most motorcycle shops out there nowadays. R.E.Cycle is "old school". It doesn't have a million dollar showroom, but more often than not it's got the parts to save your ride, and mechanics who can get it fixed when you can't. R.E.Cycle will repair almost anything. The shop was initially geared to repair and supply new and used parts for American motorcycles; Buell and Harley Davidson, and we remain focused on Harley Davidson in particular, but within a short time the demand to repair all makes and models of motorbikes was evident.

So R.E.Cycle started repairing and supplying both new and used parts and accessories for virtually all brands and types of motorcycles including: scooters, street bikes, dirt bikes, Chinese bikes, ATV’s, and even snowmobiles. R.E.Cycle has grown over its 25 years from the little shop that could, into one of the most successful bike shops on Vancouver Island.

Nicole Smith is an experienced personal injury lawyer. The majority of Nicole’s clients have been involved in accidents, (vehicle or otherwise), that have left them with significant and long-lasting injuries. Details & description:
ISL Customs Broker in Nanaimo, BC is a division of Island Shipping, which continues to be a leader in providing customs brokerage and international business importation solutions. ISL is a 100 per cent family-owned Vancouver Island customs broker firm with 50 years of experience moving freight and business goods across borders in British Columbia and throughout Canada. ISL knows no boundaries!

In today’s electronic age, you do not require your brokerage to be physically at the border crossing as was common in years gone past. Customs brokerage is now virtually a paperless transaction.
That means that whether your business is in Vancouver, Victoria, Saanich, Nanaimo, or somewhere else, ISL can be your broker while efficiently monitoring, tracing and releasing your business goods as they cross the border anywhere in Canada, via land, air or sea.
Contacting ISL is easy, by toll-free telephone, fax or e-mail.
We offer 24-hour customs broker service. Please read our international shipping FAQ‘s for more information.
If your current broker does not provide efficient, expert importing solutions then maybe it is time you called ISL Customs Brokers in Nanaimo.

?

ISL Customs Broker in Nanaimo, BC is a division of Island Shipping, which continues to be a leader in providing customs brokerage and international business importation solutions. ISL is a 100 per cent family-owned Vancouver Island customs broker firm with 50 years of experience moving freight and business goods across borders in British Columbia and throughout Canada. ISL knows no boundaries!

In today’s electronic age, you do not require your brokerage to be physically at the border crossing as was common in years gone past. Customs brokerage is now virtually a paperless transaction.
That means that whether your business is in Vancouver, Victoria, Saanich, Nanaimo, or somewhere else, ISL can be your broker while efficiently monitoring, tracing and releasing your business goods as they cross the border anywhere in Canada, via land, air or sea.
Contacting ISL is easy, by toll-free telephone, fax or e-mail.

Details & description:
Rob Janssen has always had an interest in all things mechanical - from his very first hot rod cars and motorcycles, to heavy duty equipment, farm machinery, and everything in between. In 1994 Rob Janssen established R.E.Cycle in Chemainus on Vancouver Island. It's not like most motorcycle shops out there nowadays. R.E.Cycle is "old school". It doesn't have a million dollar showroom, but more often than not it's got the parts to save your ride, and mechanics who can get it fixed when you can't. R.E.Cycle will repair almost anything. The shop was initially geared to repair and supply new and used parts for American motorcycles; Buell and Harley Davidson, and we remain focused on Harley Davidson in particular, but within a short time the demand to repair all makes and models of motorbikes was evident.

So R.E.Cycle started repairing and supplying both new and used parts and accessories for virtually all brands and types of motorcycles including: scooters, street bikes, dirt bikes, Chinese bikes, ATV’s, and even snowmobiles. R.E.Cycle has grown over its 25 years from the little shop that could, into one of the most successful bike shops on Vancouver Island.

Details & description: BIOGRAPHYOne of the most complicated military men of all time, General George Smith Patton, Jr. was born November 11, 1885 in San Gabriel, California. He was known for carrying pistols with ivory handles and his intemperate manner, and is regarded as one of the most successful United States field commanders of any war. He continually strove to train his troops to the highest standard of excellence.Patton decided during childhood that his goal in life was to become a hero. His ancestors had fought in the Revolutionary War, the Mexican War and the Civil War, and he grew up listening to stories of their brave and successful endeavors. He attended the Virginia Military Institute for one year and went on to graduate from the United States Military Academy at West Point on June 11, 1909. He was then commissioned a Second Lieutenant in the 15th cavalry Regiment.Patton married Beatrice Ayer, whom he dated while at West Point, on May 26, 1910. In 1912 he represented the United States at the Stockholm Olympics in the first Modern Pentathlon.

Details & description:
ISL Customs Broker in Nanaimo, BC is a division of Island Shipping, which continues to be a leader in providing customs brokerage and international business importation solutions. ISL is a 100 per cent family-owned Vancouver Island customs broker firm with 50 years of experience moving freight and business goods across borders in British Columbia and throughout Canada. ISL knows no boundaries!

In today’s electronic age, you do not require your brokerage to be physically at the border crossing as was common in years gone past. Customs brokerage is now virtually a paperless transaction.
That means that whether your business is in Vancouver, Victoria, Saanich, Nanaimo, or somewhere else, ISL can be your broker while efficiently monitoring, tracing and releasing your business goods as they cross the border anywhere in Canada, via land, air or sea.
Contacting ISL is easy, by toll-free telephone, fax or e-mail.
We offer 24-hour customs broker service. Please read our international shipping FAQ‘s for more information.
If your current broker does not provide efficient, expert importing solutions then maybe it is time you called ISL Customs Brokers in Nanaimo.

Details & description:
Derek Jonson practices commercial litigation with a focus on contractual matters of all description, insurance matters, commercial tenancies, professional negligence, and builders liens.
Derek has particular expertise in construction and engineering disputes. He has been involved in major litigation in that field, on behalf of owners and contractors. Derek also acts for clients involved in property insurance disputes and has notably represented claimants in large fire losses throughout British Columbia in their actions against insurers and insurance brokers.
Derek has a BSc in Mechanical Engineering (University of Manitoba, gold medalist) and a Bachelor of Laws degree (UBC). Following law school Derek clerked with the British Columbia Court of Appeal, and was called to the British Columbia Bar in 1995. He began his legal career with one of the leading large Vancouver law firms practicing construction litigation before joining Ramsay Lampman Rhodes in 1998.

RLR Lawyers (Ramsay Lampman Rhodes) is one of Vancouver Island’s largest full-service law firms. Our lawyers are recognized as leading practitioners in their respective fields. From routine matters to complex commercial transactions and personal injury claims, we offer trusted legal advice and representation to Island businesses and residents. For over 40 years our lawyers have worked to advance the interests of clients across Vancouver Island including the Comox and Alberni Valleys.

Legal excellence, business savvy and a practical outlook define our approach to client service.

The mission of the Multiple Sclerosis Society of Canada is: To be a leader in finding a cure for multiple sclerosis and enabling people affected by MS to enhance their quality of life. Our two major programs provide hope for the future through the support of MS research into the cause, treatment and cure of the disease and hope for today through our many services that assist people with MS and their families. Since our founding in 1948, the core support of the MS Society has been from tens of thousands of dedicated individuals, companies and foundations in communities across Canada. The Society receives almost no funding from government. The MS Society of Canada has a membership of 28,000. It is the only national voluntary organization in Canada that supports both MS research and services for people with MS and their families. The MS Society is governed by a National Board of Directors comprised of 27 volunteer members who are elected annually. The seven regional divisions and nearly 120 chapters are also governed by elected volunteer boards of directors. Some 1,500 volunteers serve on MS Society national, division and chapter boards and committees. An estimated 13,500 women and men are volunteers for service programs, fund raising events, public awareness campaigns and social action activities. The head office of the MS Society is located in Toronto, Ontario. Division offices are located in Dartmouth, Montreal, Toronto, Winnipeg, Regina, Edmonton, and Vancouver.

Details & description:
Appointed Queen’s Counsel in 2003, John Horn, Q.C. practices in the fields of civil litigation, mediation and arbitration. As an advocate, John has appeared in numerous civil and criminal trials before all levels of court. He is a recognized authority in the conduct and procedure of civil litigation in British Columbia, and co-author of the definitive civil procedure text for BC lawyers – the 2-volume Conduct of Civil Litigation in British Columbia, better known to other lawyers simply as “Fraser & Horn.”
John’s unique ability to draft written litigation materials which are concise, informative, and can be quickly absorbed by a busy judge or master has proved invaluable to the firm’s clients.
John was appointed a Master of the Supreme Court of British Columbia in 1989, based in Nanaimo and served the North Island area in that capacity until his retirement in 2003.

RLR Lawyers (Ramsay Lampman Rhodes) is one of Vancouver Island’s largest full-service law firms. Our lawyers are recognized as leading practitioners in their respective fields. From routine matters to complex commercial transactions and personal injury claims, we offer trusted legal advice and representation to Island businesses and residents. For over 40 years our lawyers have worked to advance the interests of clients across Vancouver Island including the Comox and Alberni Valleys.

Legal excellence, business savvy and a practical outlook define our approach to client service.

?I love changing minds about visiting the dentist. A dentist appointment doesn?t have to be a negative experience, and it?s the absolute best thing to hear one of my patients express their joy and gratitude for a painless visit.?

Whether you are looking for a new family dentist or have unresolved dental issues and want a second opinion, Dr Crapo can help. Call to schedule your complimentary consultation.  You'll be glad you did!

Details & description: We have been serving satisfied heat pump customers in Victoria for over 20 years, and will be here to look after you for many years to come. We are the only premier dealer for Lennox in Victoria, BC. A heat pump is an all-in-one cooling and heating system. During summer months, it works like an air conditioner. It extracts heat from inside your home and transfers it to the outdoor air. When the weather's cooler, it does the exact opposite, taking heat from outside and moving it inside. For optimal comfort and efficiency, a Lennox heat pump can be combined with a gas furnace in one dual-fuel system.

Details & description: BCANDS is a duly registered non-profit society (#S-27869) with a charitable tax status. We currently have over 6100 members. The mandate of the BC Aboriginal Network on Disability Society is: To Promote the Betterment of Aboriginal People with Disabilities. The organization was founded in July 1991, to deal specifically with the issues of Aboriginal People with special needs. Quote from the Honourable Ethel Blondin-Andrew, Minister of Secretary of State, Children and Youth (in an address to the BCANDS General Assembly Oct. 1995): There are few situations more challenging or more pressing than the plight of Aboriginal people living with disabilities. According to Stats Canada, about 15% of the general population are people with disabilities. We have to double that figure to get a measure of how much more serious the issues are in Aboriginal communities. Thirty-one percent of our community members live with a disability - almost a third of our population are leading lives of quiet desperation. This reality influences the life of the entire community. In Canada, we are a democracy and we are judged not only how we treat everyone but on how we treat the people who need the help the most. The weakest, and the people that are most marginalized.

Nature's Spectrum developed an objective testing procedure to gauge sauna heaters' IR output in our quest to acquire the highest performing Infrared heaters. Details & description:
Mitchell Selly obtained his law degree in 2003 from the University of Victoria and began practicing in Victoria after completing his articles in 2004. His practice is focused on representing people who have been injured due to the negligence of others. He handles motor vehicle accidents, occupier’s liability (a.k.a. slip-and-fall), and medical malpractice cases. Mitchell has helped people with a vast array of injuries, including complex brain, orthopedic, psychiatric, vestibular, and chronic pain disorders / soft tissue injuries. He currently sits on the executive council of the Victoria Bar Association and is a member of the Trial Lawyers Association of British Columbia and the Canadian Bar Association.

“I think it is important to recognize that each person’s individual characteristics can result in one person being affected very differently by an accident than another person, even though they may have suffered similar injuries. I like to get to know my clients so that I can better understand how their injuries have affected them and use that information to achieve a result that is fair in their individual circumstances.”

Details & description:
The words Love Is Round arrived in Sherry Morgan's prayer time in October, 2015. A flood of inspiration followed, including an understanding of what those words point to and why they are so important and relevant at this time. Love is Round points to a core design of our universe, which we are integrally a part of, and explains the experience people have when connecting with aspects of the natural world. Teaching people about the Phenomenon of Prayer, the core basis of which is the experience of connection with aspects of the natural world, has been Sherry’s work since 1998. Love is Round became the context for her work and the name for her website.

Details & description: Rubbish psychology 101. Over time, Mark's hauling and Recycling has learned a thing or two about rubbish. The most striking fact we uncovered was that we love our junk! We accumulate it we hang on to it, we have emotions and memories attached to it. Each item has a story to tell, it's hard to let go. But when the house is full and can't park the car in the garage anymore, the inevitable happens we snap! We want to see it all gone right now. But don't feel guilty. The renewal process has just begun. Mark's hauling and recycling will find a new purpose for all those treasures, and that's no trash.

At 1 Stop Furniture Shop, experience comfort as you are served by our friendly staff. We will explain our services and products to you including our email club that will keep you advised of our discounts. We also sell under the website names of Sidney Furniture Shop and Victoria Furniture Shop. See our current promotion. Come by and meet our friendly staff at One Stop Furniture Shop, you won't be disappointed.

Details & description:
Matthew specializes in family and immigration law. He is based in Nanaimo and was called to the BC Bar as a lawyer in 2012. He is passionate about helping his clients in a way that is best suited to resolving their legal problems. He has helped hundreds of clients solve their legal problems. If you have a family or immigration related question, then book a consultation with Matthew today! It only takes a minute.

Matthew helps his clients obtain what they are legally entitled to with the goal of improving their lives — one client at a time. His expertise in family law includes, but is not limited to, assisting clients with parenting issues, parenting time, and parental responsibilities. His expertise in immigration law includes, but is not limited to, assisting clients with visitor visas, grandparent super visas; and, spousal sponsorship.?

Matthew is a member in good standing with the:
Law Society of British Columbia;
Canadian Bar Association;
Nanaimo County Bar Association;
Nanaimo City Bar Association; and,
Nanaimo Chamber of Commerce.
?
Matthew has represented clients from Metro Vancouver and Vancouver Island in front of tribunals, at disciplinary hearings, at Provincial Court, and at the Supreme Court of British Columbia. He provides his clients with clear, concise, and understandable legal advice and he prepares potential witnesses for court and deals with witnesses, victims and their families in a considerate and courteous manner.

Matthew has represented clients with complex family claims involving spousal and child abuse. He has skillfully litigated, mediated, and negotiated claims in the Supreme Court and Provincial Court of British Columbia.

Details & description:
L. A. Limousines has been serving Victoria and Vancouver Island since 1989. We are the largest fully diversified ground transportation company on Vancouver Island.
 
Our fleet includes late model Lincoln, Lexus, and Mercedes sedans, Lincoln Navigator luxury SUVs, vans, stretch limousines, and Navigator SUV limousines. We also have Vancouver Island’s only luxury limousine buses with seating capacity for up to 26 passengers.
 
L. A. Limousines provides safe, efficient ground transportation and our goal is to exceed your expectations!

We are Different.
 
L. A. Limousines is proud to be the first limousine company in British Columbia to offer a hybrid luxury vehicle! In addition to our Lexus hybrid, our Limousine Buses run on plant-based bio-diesel. Our transportation coordinators and on-site airport greeters assist in meeting the needs of both small and large groups. From the planning stages to on-site arrival and departure coordination; we are the Vancouver Island affiliate company for several worldwide ground transportation companies.
 
We have experienced, well trained chauffeurs who are knowledgeable about our city and who take pride in making your experience a memorable one. L. A. Limousines provides safe, efficient ground transportation. Our goal is to exceed your expectations!

Details & description: What do I do? Essentially, I help people. I practice personal injury law. What does that mean? It means that I deal with any type of claim involving a person suffering injuries through the fault of another. However, I do not deal with Workers' Compensation claims. The most common type of claim is for injuries suffered in a car accident. If the accident occurred in BC then it is likely you are dealing with the ICBC. I have a great deal of experience in dealing with these claims. I also deal with claims for long term disability (LTD) benefits and Canada Pension Plan (CPP) disability benefits. My clients are located all over British Columbia and elsewhere. My general philosophy is focused upon recovery. What I mean by this is that I do whatever I can to assist clients in recovering from their injuries.

Details & description: Located in Sidney, Adel's Play N Discovery House is a B.C. licensed child care centre for 3-5 year olds. Here fun play becomes a medium of discovery and learning! We believe that children learn best in open-ended explorations, where teachers help them make meaningful connections. Our daily activities include fun play in creative arts & crafts, painting, expressive language, science play, creative counting, alphabet recognition and learning fine motor skills like cutting, knitting, handwriting and drawing shapes. To promote physical activeness or use of large muscles, our outdoor play include sand and water play, cooperative games, kite flying, nature walk, and engaging field trips to farms, aquariums, museums, parks, grocery stores, firefighter stations and others. Believing that high quality early childhood learning program should be affordable to most parents, we offer the lowest at the ranges of fees for licensed group childcare facilities in the Peninsula.

Details & description: Welcome to R&R Projectz! We specialize in cabinet refacing. What is cabinet refacing? Cabinet refacing consists of removing the old doors and drawers, replacing them with new colour coordinated doors, ranging from wood to thermofoil (PVC). We then use matching materials for the outer surfaces to match your new door choice. (This includes panels, toe-kick, and edge taping).Is refacing right for me?    Do you like your current kitchen layout?    Do your existing kitchen cabinets have that "worn out" or "outdated" appearance,     but are solidly constructed?    Do you want a fresh look for your kitchen without the cost of a whole new kitchen?     Or the time constraint of a full renovation?    Do you want to add drawers, roll-outs, lazy susans and cabinet modifications     without changing your entire kitchen?If you answered yes to any or all of these questions, then kitchen refacing is for you!

Truck #1: 
5 Ton Crane Truck with 36 feet of reach. This truck is a single axle with an 18 foot deck.

10 ton Tadano Crane Truck has 52 feet of reach with an 18 foot deck 
This crane truck is used in heavy commercial delivery.

Truck #3:

This Crane truck is used for special material handling and construction services, paper mills and the shipyard industry.

15 Ton Rough Terrain Crane, with 60 feet of boom and a 20 foot Jib.
This crane is an Industrial crane used in heavy construction, shipyards and paper mills.
 

Truck #5:
18 ton Tadano Crane truck has 82 feet of reach, and is equipped with a fifth wheel or a removable 16 ft deck.
This crane is perfect for hauling and placing trusses.

Called to the Bar in British Columbia in 1992, Robbie Sheffman practices Canadian Citizenship and Immigration Law, focusing on all Canadian citizenship, permanent residence and temporary residence matters, from the routine to the complex, as well as appeals and judicial review applications. He is a member of the executive of the Canadian Bar Association, British Columbia Branch, Immigration Subsection. Robbie has presented papers and moderated panels at British Columbia and Canadian national immigration law conferences, on such subjects as skilled worker permanent residence applications, disclosure requirements and misrepresentation, and ethics in the context of an immigration law practice. Robbie also practices Business Law, with an emphasis on corporate and commercial matters for private and institutional clients, and he advises on land use issues including land cooperatives. He has also appeared before the British Columbia Supreme Court on a wide variety of commercial and insolvency matters. He has lectured on corporate law, creditors' remedies and personal property security for the Law Society of British Columbia's Professional Legal Training Course (the bar admission course), and he is a past Instructor of Remedies and Business Associations at the University of Victoria's Faculty of Law.He was also an adjudicator of Canadian Employment Insurance appeals for nine years and is a past member of the Victoria Bar Association executive. In his spare time, Robbie plays keyboards for a rock 'n roll band, The Reverbs. He is also active in amateur sports. Prior to his law career he was a sports analyst and associate producer at TSN, Canada's national television sports network. He also led a team to successfully establish an FM radio station at Toronto's York University.

Details & description: At the Dr. Adam Pite and Dr. David S. Philip's cosmetic dental clinic we offer many services. Dr. David S. Philip is a dedicated health professional who has spent his entire practicing career improving his education and skills to give his patients functional, healthy mouths with an emphasis on appearance and cosmetics. He has been member of the American Academy of Cosmetic Dentistry (A.A.C.D.) since 1989 and was accredited by the Academy in 1992. He is examiner for Accreditation for the Academy and served as Chairman of Accreditation for two years. He is a graduate of the Las Vegas Institute for Advanced Dental Studies having successfully completed the Advanced Anterior Aesthetic program in 1999, and was successful in completing the masters program at L.V.I. in 2000. Dr. Adam W Pite is a genuine, caring dentist with a small-town personality who has had extensive experience in complex dentistry in his relatively short career. He has attended post-graduate training at Vancouver General Hospital and is a proctor with the California Centre for Advanced Dental Studies (http://www.ccads.org). Dr. Pite is trained in IV Sedation and performs surgery related to implants. He has provided oral care for the Northeastern Ontario Regional Cancer Centre, and as of January 2011, Dr. Pite provides oral care for patients of the Vancouver Island Cancer Centre. He volunteers abroad, previously in Vietnam, Cambodia and Tanzania. Toll Free: 1-800-543-9220

B C Aboriginal Network on Disability Society
Details & description: BCANDS is a duly registered non-profit society (#S-27869) with a charitable tax status. We currently have over 6100 members. The mandate of the BC Aboriginal Network on Disability Society is: To Promote the Betterment of Aboriginal People with Disabilities. The organization was founded in July 1991, to deal specifically with the issues of Aboriginal People with special needs. Quote from the Honourable Ethel Blondin-Andrew, Minister of Secretary of State, Children and Youth (in an address to the BCANDS General Assembly Oct. 1995): There are few situations more challenging or more pressing than the plight of Aboriginal people living with disabilities. According to Stats Canada, about 15% of the general population are people with disabilities. We have to double that figure to get a measure of how much more serious the issues are in Aboriginal communities. Thirty-one percent of our community members live with a disability - almost a third of our population are leading lives of quiet desperation. This reality influences the life of the entire community. In Canada, we are a democracy and we are judged not only how we treat everyone but on how we treat the people who need the help the most. The weakest, and the people that are most marginalized.

Details & description:
L. A. Limousines has been serving Victoria and Vancouver Island since 1989. We are the largest fully diversified ground transportation company on Vancouver Island.
 
Our fleet includes late model Lincoln, Lexus, and Mercedes sedans, Lincoln Navigator luxury SUVs, vans, stretch limousines, and Navigator SUV limousines. We also have Vancouver Island’s only luxury limousine buses with seating capacity for up to 26 passengers.
 
L. A. Limousines provides safe, efficient ground transportation and our goal is to exceed your expectations!

We are Different.
 
L. A. Limousines is proud to be the first limousine company in British Columbia to offer a hybrid luxury vehicle! In addition to our Lexus hybrid, our Limousine Buses run on plant-based bio-diesel. Our transportation coordinators and on-site airport greeters assist in meeting the needs of both small and large groups. From the planning stages to on-site arrival and departure coordination; we are the Vancouver Island affiliate company for several worldwide ground transportation companies.
 
We have experienced, well trained chauffeurs who are knowledgeable about our city and who take pride in making your experience a memorable one. L. A. Limousines provides safe, efficient ground transportation. Our goal is to exceed your expectations!

Details & description: Welcome aboard the Tall Ship THANE sailing daily from Empress Dock A. The Edmonton Sun writes, "the 3-Hour Sail is Victoria's Best Value". "Since 1978 the 3-Hour Sail is the best way to spend an afternoon in Victoria" reports Frommer's. Explore the beautiful Strait of Juan de Fuca famous for its killer whales, sea lions, bald eagles and incredible views. Haul the sails, take the helm, climb the rigging, ride the bowsprit, fire the cannon, do some whale watching, hang in the hammock, relax and enjoy. Bring a picnic. Alcohol is permitted. Gear provided. All ages and abilities welcome. Built by the Captain from recycled materials, THANE is modeled after Slocum's SPRAY, the first vessel to circumnavigate single-handed in 1895.

Details & description:
Welcome to A&M!
 
At A&M, we provide a holistic approach to your well being.
 
We incorporate multiple therapy techniques into each treatment to provide you the best result for your unique requirements.
 
By approaching the body as a whole and tailoring a plan to your specific requirements, all aspects of health can be improved.

A&M Holistic Wellness is a partnership between Mike & Nadine Jolly - and we also happen to be partners in life. In addition to our business, we are busy parents & active community members. We relocated to Merritt seven years ago from the Lower Mainland to raise our family in the welcoming community setting that Merritt offers.
